title: Release 0.4-14
description: Catch `getSymbols()` errors for requests with a length-1 `Symbol` vector, and throw a warning about any symbols that could not be imported.  Error if `getSymbols.yahooj()` symbol has no data.  Reorder and fix column names for `getSymbols.tiingo()`.  Fix futures and options expiry functions.  Fix getQuote.yahoo for multiple timezones.

title: Release 0.4-13
description:
Google Finance no longer provides data for historical prices or financial statements, so all Google data sources are defunct.
Add `getQuote.alphavantage()` and `getSymbols.tiingo()`.  Fix `getQuote.yahoo()`, `getSymbols.oanda()` and `getFX()`, and `saveChart()`.

title: Release 0.4-12
description:
`chartSeries()` now honors `show.grid` argument.  Thanks to Ethan Smith.
`getQuote.yahoo()` uses the new JSON API.
`getSymbols.yahoo()` is more careful about converting UNIX timestamps to character when creating the query URL.

title: Release 0.4-11
description: Add getSymbols() support for Alpha Vantage.  Return Yahoo Finance data as-is (don't un-adjust), and allow users to pass options to curl.

title: Release 0.5-0
description: Phase-in new default of `auto.assign = FALSE` for `getSymbols`.

title: Release 0.4-8
description:
Fixes
- getSymbols.google():
  - Honor all arguments set via setSymbolLookup().
  - Correctly parse dates in non-English locales.
- Fix getSymbols.oanda().
- Fix add_TA() when called from a function.
- Remove 'its' package references (it was archived).
- Update Yahoo Finance URLs to HTTPS to avoid redirect.
- Update FRED URL to avoid redirect.

Features
- Add split.adjust argument to getDividends.
- Add readme, contributing, and issue_template for GitHub.

title: Release 0.4-5
description: Fix multiple issues with RMySQL and getSymbols.FRED URL change.
